  "prompt": "Cost for 1kg of A is 260 USD and 1kg of B is 380. AB is made by mixing A and B. If 1kg of AB costs 300, what was the ratio that A and B has mixed?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) Let the ratio of A:B be x:y (where x = weight of A, y = weight of B)\n\n2) Total weight of the mixture = 1 kg\n\n3) Cost equation:\n   \u2022 Cost of A per kg = 260 USD\n   \u2022 Cost of B per kg = 380 USD\n   \u2022 Cost of mixture per kg = 300 USD\n\n4) Cost balance equation:\n   (260x + 380y) \u00f7 (x + y) = 300\n\n5) Cross multiply:\n   260x + 380y = 300(x + y)\n   260x + 380y = 300x + 300y\n\n6) Rearrange:\n   260x + 380y = 300x + 300y\n\n7) Subtract 260x and 300y from both sides:\n   80y = 40x\n\n8) Divide both sides by 40:\n   2y = x\n\n9) Simplified ratio:\n   A : B = 2 : 1\n\nTherefore, the mixture contains 2 parts A for every 1 part B.\n\nThe answer is 2:1.",
